# Research

When conducting research, technical investigations, or literature surveys:

- Store all research in `research/<YYYY-MM-DD>/` using today's date.
- Use kebab-case markdown filenames (e.g., `research/2026-04-03/deferred-reference-counting.md`).
- Include citations with URLs for all claims — papers, official docs, blog posts.
- When multiple topics are researched, create one file per topic, plus a
  `synthesis-and-recommendations.md` that ties them together and indexes all files.
- Research documents capture external findings. Plans capture internal design decisions. Keep them
  in their respective directories.
